    N2 · ENTITY-SCALE      · 100-1000 simultaneously-active entities · query @ ≥ 144 Hz
    N3 · PROCGEN-INFINITY  · chunk-streaming · deterministic seed · ∞-world-extent · ≤ 4 ms/chunk amortized
    N4 · GENRE-BLENDING    · hot-swap behavior-tree + aesthetic-axes at runtime · ≤ 2-frame transition
    N5 · COORDINATION      · CPU↔GPU↔RAM↔queues fully-tandem · ¬ idle-cycles ¬ stalls
                              measured-by : per-pass GPU timer ≤ budget · CPU-record-overlap-with-GPU-execute
    N6 · SOVEREIGNTY       · zero-Rust at runtime · csslc self-hosts · this is the t∞ goal
    
    each item-block below declares which north-stars it serves : [N1, N2, ...]
    items that serve NO north-star directly are correctness/tooling/foundational · still ship · just
    don't claim performance-impact they don't deliver
  ⟧

§I WORK-STYLE-FOR-EXECUTING-AGENT · how-to-think-while-shipping-this
  ⟦
    PRINCIPLE-1 · CRITICAL-THINKING-NOT-COMPLIANCE
      Every instruction Apocky or Tech-Lead gives is a HYPOTHESIS to test ¬ a fact to obey.
      If you find a constraint that makes an instruction wrong-shape · SAY SO with the constraint.
      Reza demonstrated this on v1 of this very file · 6 critiques accepted · this is the loop.
      ¬ flattery · ¬ silent-disagreement · ¬ token-burn-pretending-to-comply

    PRINCIPLE-2 · CHALLENGE-INPUTS-WITH-CSL-REASONING
      Before executing each item · open §RZ block · reason in CSL3 dense notation :
        §RZ
        item-N · what-it-claims-to-do
        what-could-make-this-wrong : enumerate failure-modes
        what-evidence-would-confirm : list ASSERTs
        what's-the-cheapest-falsification : pick one ASSERT first
        if-it-fails : adjust the item before continuing
      this is how the WinMain bug should have been caught · don't let it ship again

    PRINCIPLE-3 · PARALLELIZE-WITHIN-PHASE-DEPENDENCY-GRAPHS
      Each phase has a stated dependency graph. Items at the SAME graph-depth are independent.
      Spawn parallel agents on independent items. The bottleneck is the deepest critical-path item.
      Wall-clock = critical-path-length · NOT sum-of-item-hours.

    PRINCIPLE-4 · DISK-FIRST · SPEC-FIRST
      ¬ artifact for documents · write to CSSLv3/specs/NN_*.csl per spec-64 discipline
      every new mechanism gets a CSL spec authored BEFORE the Rust/CSSL code that implements it
      OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS section is mandatory · structural-equivalents acceptable per audit-log

    PRINCIPLE-5 · SENTINEL-BUILD-CHECK-IS-ALWAYS-ON
      scripts/sentinel_build_check.sh runs on every csslc-built .exe in CI (Gate-E)
      if a build emits an .exe that exits 0 in <50ms with empty output · the gate fails the build
      this is the WinMain-class structural defense · do not disable · do not work-around

    PRINCIPLE-6 · AI-CO-AUTHORSHIP-FIRST-CLASS
      Reza · Claude · Lazarus-fleet-instances all qualify as reviewers per spec-64 §FM.06
      attribute reviewers in lifecycle-history trailers · ¬ pretend solo-authorship
      cross-review between agents is encouraged · catches own-blindspots

    PRINCIPLE-7 · STOP-WHEN-WRONG
      if mid-item you discover the item is wrong-shape · STOP · amend the spec · do not ship-around
      "spec-amendment-via-lifecycle" is the supported path · taking a shortcut is how barnacles grow
      this is the v9→v10→v13 fork-pattern at item-granularity

    PRINCIPLE-8 · OBSERVE-DON'T-INFER
      verify mechanically · don't reason-about-correctness-from-types-alone
      ASSERT.X clauses must run in CI · golden-file diffs · validator outputs · perf-timers
      the WinMain bug taught us : the type-system can be correct and the binary still dead-code

    PRINCIPLE-9 · COORDINATION-OVER-OPTIMIZATION
      Optimizing one component without coordinating with neighbors creates seams · seams cost frames.
      Items in category-4 (GPU-driven-orchestration) are LOAD-BEARING for north-star N5.
      When in doubt · choose the option that tightens coordination · ¬ the option that micro-wins one component.

    PRINCIPLE-10 · NORTH-STAR-RANKED-TIE-BREAKS
      If two items conflict on resource (time · memory · API surface) · break ties by north-star tag :
        N1 (frame-rate) > N2 (entities) > N3 (procgen) > N4 (genre-blend) > N5 (coord) > N6 (sovereignty)
      this ordering = revenue-readiness order · ship-visibility first · purity last
  ⟧

