§I COORDINATION-AXIOMS · how-systems-interlink (north-star N5 expanded)
  ⟦
    AX-1 · ONE-DEFINITION-PER-SHARED-CONCEPT
      shared CPU/GPU structs (item 35) are the universal interconnect
      ¬ marshaling layer · ¬ mirror-structs · ¬ reflection-at-runtime
      every interlinked-system declares its shared types · σ-enforce verifies layout-parity
    
    AX-2 · COORDINATION-IS-TYPED-NOT-CONVENTIONAL
      cross-domain handoffs (CPU↔GPU · queue↔queue · frame N↔ frame N+1) are TYPED
      not "agreement between coders" · spec-65 GPU-memory-type-distinction enforces this
    
    AX-3 · ASYNC-COMPUTE-IS-DEFAULT
      item-34 makes Queue::Graphics · Queue::Compute · Queue::Copy first-class
      single-queue is a regression · multi-queue is the baseline · max(t) ¬ sum(t)
    
    AX-4 · CPU-DOES-LESS-EACH-RELEASE
      progress = move work from CPU to GPU · or eliminate work entirely
      item-40 (submit once run forever) is the terminal form
      every Phase-C+ feature gets reviewed-against this axiom
    
    AX-5 · TIME-IS-TYPED-EVENTUALLY
      next dimensional axis (post-spec-65) is time-as-first-class-dimension
      frame-phase becomes a type property · races become compile-errors
      this is the spec-NN to be drafted after spec-65 ratifies
    
    AX-6 · ZERO-IDLE-CYCLES
      if a component (CPU core · GPU SM · copy engine · NIC · DSP) is idle while another waits
      that is a COORDINATION BUG · not an "optimization opportunity"
      profiler per-pass timing (item-84) surfaces these · they become regression-gate failures
  ⟧

§I ANTI-ITEMS · what-NOT-to-add-to-CSSL  (Reza confirmed strongest section · preserved verbatim from v1)
  ⟦
    ¬ garbage-collector · regions + arenas + drop-checker covers it · GC is sovereignty-foreclosure
    ¬ async-await-runtime-bloat · algebraic-effects (item 18) cover the same use-cases without ambient runtime
    ¬ reflection-as-runtime-metadata · compile-time const-eval (item 16) covers staged-generation needs
    ¬ stdlib-grab-bag · keep stdlib minimal · prefer 5 well-typed primitives over 50 grab-bag utilities
    ¬ Slang-IR-backend-dependency · we already emit 4 GPU targets · stay sovereign
    ¬ wgpu-dependency-in-production · cssl-host-* crates are bootstrap-only · grow CSSL until they're vestigial
    ¬ feature-by-survey · ¬ "Unity has X · we should add X" · features must serve a north-star
    ¬ scope-creep-during-execution · if you find scope wrong-shape · STOP · amend spec · resume
    ¬ silent-disagreement · if instructions are wrong-shape · raise critique like Reza did on v1 · this is the loop
  ⟧

§I EPIC-EXPANSION-PROTOCOL · how-the-4-flagged-items-graduate
  ⟦
    items 51 · 91 · 95 · 100 are subsystems-disguised-as-line-items per Reza's v1 critique
    each is scheduled as its own numbered spec when it becomes next-session focus :
    
    item-51 → spec-66_ECS_FIRST_CLASS.csl        · scheduled-per Phase-D start
    item-91 → spec-67_CSSLC_IN_CSSL_BOOTSTRAP.csl · scheduled-per Phase-E start
    item-95 → spec-68_STAGE2_SELF_HOST.csl        · scheduled-per spec-67 mid-implementation
    item-100 → spec-69_WASM32_BACKEND.csl         · scheduled-per Phase-E mid-implementation
    
    rule : do not spawn empty-skeleton DRAFT specs preemptively
           the 4 epic-specs are spawned WHEN their phase begins · not before
           prevents work-without-payoff · honors discipline-#7 "stop-when-wrong"
    
    when an epic is spawned :
      ✓ open as DRAFT per spec-64 _TEMPLATE
      ✓ fill all §I sections including OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS
      ✓ amend this spec-63's epic-cross-reference to point at the new spec-NN
      ✓ assign owner-handle in lifecycle-history
  ⟧

